<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA: SOCCER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tom Crane made the University of San Diego's only goal as the Toreros defeated 
visiting Brigham Young, 1-0. Midfielder Crane headed the ball into the net on 
an assist by Andrew Kummer in the first half. 
</P>
<P>
SAN DIEGO STATE 
</P>
<P>
The men's soccer and women's volleyball teams will play against alumni teams 
Saturday. The soccer game will be at 6 p.m. at the Aztec Bowl, the volleyball 
game at 7:30 p.m. at Peterson Gym. 
</P>
</TEXT>
