</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: POP/ROCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CLAUDIA PUIG and DANIEL CERONE, Arts and entertainment reports from The 
Times, national and international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Paul McCartney will kick off his first U.S. tour in 13 years Nov. 27 to 29 at 
the Forum in Inglewood, the ex-Beatle announced Thursday at a New York press 
conference. Those dates will launch a three-week, five-city North American 
swing that will touch down in Chicago, Toronto, Montreal and New York's Madison 
Square Garden. Tickets for the Forum shows will go on sale Monday at 9 a.m. at 
Ticketmaster locations, with numbered priority wristbands handed out randomly 
at 8 a.m. CLAUDIA PUIG and DANIEL CERONE 
</P>
</TEXT>
