<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CLAUDIA PUIG and DANIEL CERONE, Arts and entertainment reports from The 
Times, national and international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MTV is telling it like it is. The cable music channel will premiere "MTV News 
at Night" on Monday at 8:30 p.m. The half-hour nightly news show will feature a 
cast of reporters covering breaking rock 'n' roll, entertainment, style and pop 
culture feature stories of interest to MTV's young adult audience. "Unlike 
MTV's 'The Week in Rock,' our weekly retrospective of rock 'n' roll news, 'MTV 
News at Night' will include more live action and less pre-produced segments," 
said Linda Corradina, vice president, MTV News. CLAUDIA PUIG and DANIEL CERONE 
</P>
