<P>
PAC BELL WINS ON DIAL-PORN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pacific Bell is one step closer to pulling the plug on so-called "dial-a-porn" 
telephone services after a favorable ruling in federal court, a company 
spokeswoman said. A federal judge in Washington ruled that Pacific Bell, as a 
private business, has the right to disconnect dial-a-porn services under 
federal laws. However, the utility must now determine if it has the same rights 
under state laws and filed a suit in San Francisco Superior Court, naming 13 
dial-a-porn companies as defendants. Past efforts to ban dial-a-porn services 
have been blocked by First Amendment guarantees of free speech. "As a private 
business, Pac Bell should have the right to choose who we want and don't want 
to do business with," Pacific Bell spokeswoman Kathleen Flynn said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
