<HEADLINE>
<P>
QUAYLE DENIES LOOKING FOR ORANGE COUNTY HOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
During a visit to Orange County, Vice President Dan Quayle scotched rumors 
Thursday that he and his wife, Marilyn, are looking for a vacation home in the 
county. 
</P>
<P>
"We love to be here, but I don't think it is in the cards right now," Quayle 
said, dashing the hopes of the dozens of real estate agents who have called the 
White House in recent weeks offering to help the Quayles locate a second home 
in California. But he added, "Orange County is a wonderful place to be. 
Wonderful weather, wonderful people." 
</P>
<P>
Quayle made the comments as he arrived at a $500-per-person dinner at a Newport 
Beach restaurant, the second of two events he attended to help the Orange 
County and California Republican Party organizations raise money. 
</P>
<P>
A Quayle adviser said in July that the vice president was considering buying a 
home in California as a retreat. 
</P>
