<HEADLINE>
<P>
TYGER, DUKE TO BUILD CO-GENERATION PLANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SPARTANBURG, S.C. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tyger Construction Co., in a joint venture with Duke Engineering &amp; Services 
Inc., on Tuesday announced the award of a $116-million contract to design and 
build a 128-megawatt co-generation power plant near Clarksville, Va. 
</P>
<P>
Under the terms of the contract, Tyger Construction and Duke Engineering, an 
affiliate of Duke Power Co. with headquarters in Charlotte, will build the 
facility as a turnkey project. Tyger will be general contractor, sharing 
procurement responsibilities with Duke Engineering. Duke will be responsible 
for overall project management and design through the start-up of the 
coal-fired facility. 
</P>
</TEXT>
