<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: GLENDALE MAN SHOT TO DEATH IN INGLEWOOD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Glendale man was fatally shot in Inglewood during an argument with another 
man, Inglewood police said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Arnaldo Pimentel, 28, was pronounced dead about 6:40 p.m. Wednesday at Martin 
Luther King Jr.-Drew Medical Center, Sgt. Harold Moret said. Pimentel was shot 
several times in the upper body about 5:30 p.m. while arguing with a man on a 
sidewalk in the 3800 block of 111th Place, he said. 
</P>
<P>
Police were looking for the gunman, who fled in a car. Moret said it was not 
known what the men were arguing about. 
</P>
<P>
"There were witnesses who saw them drive up together," Moret said. "They were 
there for some time. Nobody paid any attention until 30 or 40 minutes later 
when they heard gunshots." 
</P>
