SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 72-year-old East San Diego man was robbed and his 65-year-old neighbor raped 
by an armed robber. 
</P>
<P>
Police said the victims returned at 9:30 p.m. Wednesday after eating dinner and 
the man went inside the house for a moment while the woman waited outside. The 
man was confronted by an armed robber who had entered the house through an open 
window. 
</P>
<P>
According to a police account of the incident, the robber held a gun to the 
victim's head and ordered him to call the woman inside. The assailant robbed 
the man of about $56, locked him in a back bedroom and raped the woman, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
After the attack, the man took the rape victim to a hospital, where she was 
treated and released, and notified police. 
</P>
