<P>
TERESCHUK TO COACH LAGUNA HILLS BASEBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Laguna Hills High School has hired Pete Tereschuk to coach baseball, Athletic 
Director Dave Brown said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Tereschuk, junior varsity coach at Lakewood High School the past two years, 
replaces Jack Hodges, who resigned after 10 seasons to become baseball coach at 
Saddleback College. 
</P>
<P>
Tereschuk was varsity coach at Long Beach Wilson from 1982-1987. He also has 
been an assistant at San Diego State. 
</P>
<P>
"We think he had a good combination of experience," Brown said. 
</P>
<P>
Tereschuk also will teach English and assist with the varsity football program, 
which Brown said was influential in his selection. 
</P>
